Introduction of pyhton:- Python is a high-level, interpreted, and general-purpose programming language known for its simplicity and readability. It was created by Guido van Rossum and first released in 1991.

Features of Python

Python has many powerful features that make it one of the most popular programming languages.

1. Simple and Easy to Learn :-

Python uses clear and readable syntax, making it beginner-friendly.  

2. Interpreted Language :-

Python code is executed line by line by an interpreter, so there is no need for compilation before running the program.

3. High-Level Language :-

Python handles complex tasks like memory management automatically, allowing programmers to focus on problem-solving.

4. Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) :-

Python supports classes, objects, inheritance, polymorphism, and encapsulation.

5. Platform Independent :-

Python programs can run on Windows, Linux, and macOS without major changes.

6. Dynamically Typed :-

You do not need to declare the type of a variable.

 Advantages of Python :-

1. Easy to learn and use
2.Large library ecosystem
3.Portable across platforms
4.Supports multiple programming paradigms
5. Strong community support

Disadvantages of Python :-

1. Slower than compiled languages like C++
2. Higher memory consumption
3. Not ideal for mobile app development

